{"questionId":"11880","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{2{x^2} - 5x - 12}}{{x + 2}}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,x \\in \\mathbb{R}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,x \\ne&nbsp; - 2\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>≠</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>As&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\to&nbsp; \\pm \\infty \">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;approaches an oblique straight line asymptote.</p>\n<p>Divide&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{x^2} - 5x - 12\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n</math></span> by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x + 2\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;to find the equation of this asymptote.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = 2x - 9 + \\frac{6}{{x + 2}}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>So equation of asymptote is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 2x - 9\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11880","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.5c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"As x → ± ∞ the graph of f ( x ) approaches an oblique straight line asymptote. Divide 2 x 2 − 5 x − 12 by x + 2 to find the equation of this asymptote.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.13—Rational functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}